4 5. Have completed the curricular requirements for admission to
5 an institution within The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education
6 or have completed the core curriculum and be seeking admission to a
7 technology center school governed by the State Board of Career and
8 Technology Education. Students shall also have attained a 2.5 grade
9 point average in the core Oklahoma’s Promise required curriculum
10 courses. Students who attended a high school which did not offer
11 all the core Oklahoma’s Promise required curriculum courses or
12 students who were educated by other means and were not offered all
13 the core Oklahoma’s Promise required curriculum courses shall be
14 allowed to satisfy this curriculum requirement by participating in a
15 program approved by the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education
