7 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Higher Learning Access Program;
amending 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2603, as last amended by Section 1,
8 Chapter 485, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 2603), which
relates to eligibility requirements; adding technology center school
9 education to eligibility; updating references; expanding eligibility
for students in the court-ordered custody of a private nonprofit
10 child-placing agency or a federally recognized Indian tribe during
certain time; defining who a parent is for a child of a certified
11 teacher; amending 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2605, as last amended by
Section 2, Chapter 485, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
12 2605), which relates to student agreements; updating references;
expanding eligibility for students in the court-ordered custody of a
13 private nonprofit child-placing agency or a federally recognized
Indian tribe during certain time; removing income requirement for
14 student in the custody of the Oklahoma Department of Human Services,
in the court-ordered custody of a private nonprofit child-placing
15 agency, or a federally recognized Indian tribe during certain time;
requiring Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education verify
16 standard or alternative certificate is in a classroom subject;
expanding definition of certified teacher; clarifying computation of
17 employment for purposes of eligibility; requiring standard or
alternative certification be in a classroom subject as determined by
18 the State Regents; clarifying effect of service as an emergency or
provisionally certified teacher; increasing financial need
19 qualification threshold amount on or after certain school year;
amending 62 O.S. 2021, Section 34.87, as amended by Section 1,
20 Chapter 409, O.S.L. 2024 (62 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 34.87), which
relates to the transfer of funds to the Higher Learning Access Trust
21 Fund; requiring certain calculations utilizing certain
methodologies; requiring certain calculated amounts be reported to
22 certain Boards; clarifying transfer determination; providing an
effective date; and providing a conditional effective date.
